messages.message:
Seeing a bunch of pip install version mismatches. Anyone know how they should be resolved?
```
ERROR: textract 1.6.1 has requirement beautifulsoup4==4.5.3, but you'll have beautifulsoup4 4.6.0 which is inco
mpatible.
ERROR: textract 1.6.1 has requirement chardet==2.3.0, but you'll have chardet 3.0.4 which is incompatible.
ERROR: textract 1.6.1 has requirement six==1.10.0, but you'll have six 1.12.0 which is incompatible.
ERROR: textract 1.6.1 has requirement xlrd==1.0.0, but you'll have xlrd 1.1.0 which is incompatible.
ERROR: tensorflow-tensorboard 1.5.1 has requirement bleach==1.5.0, but you'll have bleach 2.1.3 which is incom$
atible.
ERROR: tensorflow-tensorboard 1.5.1 has requirement html5lib==0.9999999, but you'll have html5lib 1.0.1 which $
s incompatible.
```
I’ve never not seen those, so I assumed they were red herrings.
Well it ends up causing a bunch of libraries to get uninstalled like six-1.12 and dateutil-2.8.0.
Oh interesting. I didn’t know that was why, but I did end up working around that by reinstalling them after the requirements.txt step
